ZEQ2-Lite
Open-sourced and mod expandable project based on a highly modified ioQuake3 engine foundation and features many true-to-reference DBZ visuals and mechanics. Developer sandbox for people who want to tinker with basic game development.

119 #define TAG(_a, _b, _c, _d) (ULONG) \
120  (((_a) << 0) + ((_b) << 8) + ((_c) << 16) + ((_d) << 24))
121 
122 #ifdef __GNUC__
123 static __inline struct _KPCR * KeGetCurrentKPCR(
124  VOID)
125 {
126  ULONG Value;
127 
128  __asm__ __volatile__ (
129 #if (__GNUC__ >= 3)
130  /* support -masm=intel */
131  "mov{l} {%%fs:0x18, %0|%0, %%fs:0x18}\n\t"
132 #else
133  "movl %%fs:0x18, %0\n\t"
134 #endif
135  : "=r" (Value)
136  : /* no inputs */
137  );
138  return (struct _KPCR *) Value;
139 }
140 
141 #elif defined( __WATCOMC__ )
142 
143 extern struct _KPCR * KeGetCurrentKPCR( void );
144 #pragma aux KeGetCurrentKPCR = \
145  "mov eax, fs:[0x18]" \
146  value [ eax ];
147 
148 #endif

4116 static __inline PSINGLE_LIST_ENTRY
4117 PopEntryList(
4118  /*IN*/ PSINGLE_LIST_ENTRY ListHead)
4119 {
4120  PSINGLE_LIST_ENTRY Entry;
4121 
4122  Entry = ListHead->Next;
4123  if (Entry != NULL)
4124  {
4125  ListHead->Next = Entry->Next;
4126  }
4127  return Entry;
4128 }
4129 
4130 /*
4131  * VOID
4132  * PushEntryList(
4133  * IN PSINGLE_LIST_ENTRY ListHead,
4134  * IN PSINGLE_LIST_ENTRY Entry)
4135  */
4136 #define PushEntryList(_ListHead, \
4137  _Entry) \
4138 { \
4139  (_Entry)->Next = (_ListHead)->Next; \
4140  (_ListHead)->Next = (_Entry); \
4141 }
4142 
4143 /*
4144  * VOID
4145  * RemoveEntryList(
4146  * IN PLIST_ENTRY Entry)
4147  */
4148 #define RemoveEntryList(_Entry) \
4149 { \
4150  PLIST_ENTRY _OldFlink; \
4151  PLIST_ENTRY _OldBlink; \
4152  _OldFlink = (_Entry)->Flink; \
4153  _OldBlink = (_Entry)->Blink; \
4154  _OldFlink->Blink = _OldBlink; \
4155  _OldBlink->Flink = _OldFlink; \
4156  (_Entry)->Flink = NULL; \
4157  (_Entry)->Blink = NULL; \
4158 }
4159 
4160 static __inline PLIST_ENTRY
4161 RemoveHeadList(
4162  /*IN*/ PLIST_ENTRY ListHead)
4163 {
4164  PLIST_ENTRY OldFlink;
4165  PLIST_ENTRY OldBlink;
4166  PLIST_ENTRY Entry;
4167 
4168  Entry = ListHead->Flink;
4169  OldFlink = ListHead->Flink->Flink;
4170  OldBlink = ListHead->Flink->Blink;
4171  OldFlink->Blink = OldBlink;
4172  OldBlink->Flink = OldFlink;
4173 
4174  if (Entry != ListHead)
4175  {
4176  Entry->Flink = NULL;
4177  Entry->Blink = NULL;
4178  }
4179 
4180  return Entry;
4181 }
4182 
4183 static __inline PLIST_ENTRY
4184 RemoveTailList(
4185  /*IN*/ PLIST_ENTRY ListHead)
4186 {
4187  PLIST_ENTRY OldFlink;
4188  PLIST_ENTRY OldBlink;
4189  PLIST_ENTRY Entry;
4190 
4191  Entry = ListHead->Blink;
4192  OldFlink = ListHead->Blink->Flink;
4193  OldBlink = ListHead->Blink->Blink;
4194  OldFlink->Blink = OldBlink;
4195  OldBlink->Flink = OldFlink;
4196 
4197  if (Entry != ListHead)
4198  {
4199  Entry->Flink = NULL;
4200  Entry->Blink = NULL;
4201  }
4202 
4203  return Entry;
4204 }

5119 ExInterlockedPopEntrySList(

5121  /*IN*/ PKSPIN_LOCK Lock);

5123 
5124 NTOSAPI
5125 PSINGLE_LIST_ENTRY
5126 DDKFASTAPI
5127 ExInterlockedPushEntrySList(
5128  /*IN*/ PSLIST_HEADER ListHead,
5129  /*IN*/ PSINGLE_LIST_ENTRY ListEntry,
5130  /*IN*/ PKSPIN_LOCK Lock);
5131 
5132 
5133 #if (__USE_NTOSKRNL__) && (_WIN32_WINNT >= 0x0501)
5134 #define ExInterlockedPopEntrySList(_ListHead, \
5135  _Lock) \
5136  InterlockedPopEntrySList(_ListHead)
5137 
5138 #define ExInterlockedPushEntrySList(_ListHead, \
5139  _ListEntry, \
5140  _Lock) \
5141  InterlockedPushEntrySList(_ListHead, _ListEntry)
5142 #endif /* __USE_NTOSKRNL__ */
5143 
5144 #define ExQueryDepthSList(ListHead) QueryDepthSList(ListHead)
5145 
5146 static __inline PVOID
5147 ExAllocateFromNPagedLookasideList(
5148  /*IN*/ PNPAGED_LOOKASIDE_LIST Lookaside)
5149 {
5150  PVOID Entry;
5151 
5152  Lookaside->TotalAllocates++;
5153  Entry = ExInterlockedPopEntrySList(&Lookaside->ListHead,
5154  &Lookaside->Obsoleted);
5155  if (Entry == NULL) {
5156  Lookaside->_DDK_DUMMYUNION_MEMBER(AllocateMisses)++;
5157  Entry = (Lookaside->Allocate)(Lookaside->Type,
5158  Lookaside->Size,
5159  Lookaside->Tag);
5160  }
5161  return Entry;
5162 }
5163 
5164 static __inline VOID
5165 ExFreeToNPagedLookasideList(
5166  /*IN*/ PNPAGED_LOOKASIDE_LIST Lookaside,
5167  /*IN*/ PVOID Entry)
5168 {
5169  Lookaside->TotalFrees++;
5170  if (ExQueryDepthSList(&Lookaside->ListHead) >= Lookaside->Depth) {
5171  Lookaside->_DDK_DUMMYUNION_N_MEMBER(2,FreeMisses)++;
5172  (Lookaside->Free)(Entry);
5173  } else {
5174  ExInterlockedPushEntrySList(&Lookaside->ListHead,
5175  (PSLIST_ENTRY)Entry,
5176  &Lookaside->Obsoleted);
5177  }
5178 }
5179 
5180 #if (__USE_NTOSKRNL__) && (_WIN32_WINNT >= 0x0501)
5181 
5182 static __inline PVOID
5183 ExAllocateFromPagedLookasideList(
5184  /*IN*/ PPAGED_LOOKASIDE_LIST Lookaside)
5185 {
5186  PVOID Entry;
5187 
5188  Lookaside->TotalAllocates++;
5189  Entry = InterlockedPopEntrySList(&Lookaside->ListHead);
5190  if (Entry == NULL) {
5191  Lookaside->_DDK_DUMMYUNION_MEMBER(AllocateMisses)++;
5192  Entry = (Lookaside->Allocate)(Lookaside->Type,
5193  Lookaside->Size,
5194  Lookaside->Tag);
5195  }
5196  return Entry;
5197 }
5198 
5199 static __inline VOID
5200 ExFreeToPagedLookasideList(
5201  /*IN*/ PPAGED_LOOKASIDE_LIST Lookaside,
5202  /*IN*/ PVOID Entry)
5203 {
5204  Lookaside->TotalFrees++;
5205  if (ExQueryDepthSList(&Lookaside->ListHead) >= Lookaside->Depth) {
5206  Lookaside->_DDK_DUMMYUNION_N_MEMBER(2,FreeMisses)++;
5207  (Lookaside->Free)(Entry);
5208  } else {
5209  InterlockedPushEntrySList(&Lookaside->ListHead,
5210  (PSLIST_ENTRY)Entry);
5211  }
5212 }
5213 
5214 #else /* (__USE_NTOSKRNL__) && (_WIN32_WINNT >= 0x0501) */
5215

6191  ((_Irp)->Tail.Overlay.CurrentStackLocation)
6192 
6193 /*
6194  * PIO_STACK_LOCATION
6195  * IoGetNextIrpStackLocation(
6196  * IN PIRP Irp)
6197  */
6198 #define IoGetNextIrpStackLocation(_Irp) \
6199  ((_Irp)->Tail.Overlay.CurrentStackLocation - 1)
6200 
6201 /*
6202  * VOID
6203  * IoCopyCurrentIrpStackLocationToNext(
6204  * IN PIRP Irp)
6205  */
6206 #define IoCopyCurrentIrpStackLocationToNext(_Irp) \
6207 { \
6208  PIO_STACK_LOCATION _IrpSp; \
6209  PIO_STACK_LOCATION _NextIrpSp; \
6210  _IrpSp = IoGetCurrentIrpStackLocation(_Irp); \
6211  _NextIrpSp = IoGetNextIrpStackLocation(_Irp); \
6212  RtlCopyMemory(_NextIrpSp, _IrpSp, \
6213  FIELD_OFFSET(IO_STACK_LOCATION, CompletionRoutine)); \
6214  _NextIrpSp->Control = 0; \
6215 }

6887 /*
6888  * PDRIVER_CANCEL
6889  * IoSetCancelRoutine(
6890  * IN PIRP Irp,
6891  * IN PDRIVER_CANCEL CancelRoutine)
6892  */
6893 #define IoSetCancelRoutine(_Irp, \
6894  _CancelRoutine) \
6895  ((PDRIVER_CANCEL) InterlockedExchangePointer( \
6896  (PVOID *) &(_Irp)->CancelRoutine, (PVOID) (_CancelRoutine)))
6897 
6898 /*
6899  * VOID
6900  * IoSetCompletionRoutine(
6901  * IN PIRP Irp,
6902  * IN PIO_COMPLETION_ROUTINE CompletionRoutine,
6903  * IN PVOID Context,
6904  * IN BOOLEAN InvokeOnSuccess,
6905  * IN BOOLEAN InvokeOnError,
6906  * IN BOOLEAN InvokeOnCancel)
6907  */
6908 #define IoSetCompletionRoutine(_Irp, \
6909  _CompletionRoutine, \
6910  _Context, \
6911  _InvokeOnSuccess, \
6912  _InvokeOnError, \
6913  _InvokeOnCancel) \
6914 { \
6915  PIO_STACK_LOCATION _IrpSp; \
6916  ASSERT(_InvokeOnSuccess || _InvokeOnError || _InvokeOnCancel ? \
6917  _CompletionRoutine != NULL : TRUE); \
6918  _IrpSp = IoGetNextIrpStackLocation(_Irp); \
6919  _IrpSp->CompletionRoutine = (PIO_COMPLETION_ROUTINE)(_CompletionRoutine); \
6920  _IrpSp->Context = (_Context); \
6921  _IrpSp->Control = 0; \
6922  if (_InvokeOnSuccess) _IrpSp->Control = SL_INVOKE_ON_SUCCESS; \
6923  if (_InvokeOnError) _IrpSp->Control |= SL_INVOKE_ON_ERROR; \
6924  if (_InvokeOnCancel) _IrpSp->Control |= SL_INVOKE_ON_CANCEL; \
6925 }

8012 /*
8013  * ULONG
8014  * ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES(
8015  * IN PVOID Va,
8016  * IN ULONG Size)
8017  */
8018 #define ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES(_Va, \
8019  _Size) \
8020  ((ULONG) ((((ULONG_PTR) (_Va) & (PAGE_SIZE - 1)) \
8021  + (_Size) + (PAGE_SIZE - 1)) >> PAGE_SHIFT))
8022 
8023 /*
8024  * VOID
8025  * MmInitializeMdl(
8026  * IN PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
8027  * IN PVOID BaseVa,
8028  * IN SIZE_T Length)
8029  */
8030 #define MmInitializeMdl(_MemoryDescriptorList, \
8031  _BaseVa, \
8032  _Length) \
8033 { \
8034  (_MemoryDescriptorList)->Next = (PMDL) NULL; \
8035  (_MemoryDescriptorList)->Size = (CSHORT) (sizeof(MDL) + \
8036  (sizeof(PFN_NUMBER) * ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES(_BaseVa, _Length))); \
8037  (_MemoryDescriptorList)->MdlFlags = 0; \
8038  (_MemoryDescriptorList)->StartVa = (PVOID) PAGE_ALIGN(_BaseVa); \
8039  (_MemoryDescriptorList)->ByteOffset = BYTE_OFFSET(_BaseVa); \
8040  (_MemoryDescriptorList)->ByteCount = (ULONG) _Length; \
8041 }

8154 /*
8155  * VOID
8156  * MmPrepareMdlForReuse(
8157  * IN PMDL Mdl)
8158  */
8159 #define MmPrepareMdlForReuse(_Mdl) \
8160 { \
8161  if (((_Mdl)->MdlFlags & MDL_PARTIAL_HAS_BEEN_MAPPED) != 0) { \
8162  ASSERT(((_Mdl)->MdlFlags & MDL_PARTIAL) != 0); \
8163  MmUnmapLockedPages((_Mdl)->MappedSystemVa, (_Mdl)); \
8164  } else if (((_Mdl)->MdlFlags & MDL_PARTIAL) == 0) { \
8165  ASSERT(((_Mdl)->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) == 0); \
8166  } \
8167 }
